[{"c":"<p>Song Number : 22</p>"},{"c":"<p>I will sing of my Redeemer</p><p>and his wondrous love to me;</p><p>on the cruel cross he suffered,</p><p>from the curse to set me free.</p><p>Sing, O sing of my Redeemer!</p><p>With his blood he purchased me;</p><p>on the cross he sealed my pardon,</p><p>paid the debt, and made me free.</p>"},{"c":"<p>I will tell the wondrous story,</p><p>how my lost estate to save,</p><p>in his boundless love and mercy,</p><p>he the ransom freely gave.</p><p>I will praise my dear Redeemer,</p><p>his triumphant power I'll tell:</p><p>how the victory he gives me</p><p>over sin and death and hell.</p>"},{"c":"<p>I will sing of my Redeemer</p><p>and his heavenly love for me;</p><p>he from death to life has brought me,</p><p>Son of God, with him to be.</p><p>Sing, O sing of my Redeemer!</p><p>With his blood he purchased me;</p><p>on the cross he sealed my pardon,</p><p>paid the debt, and made me free.</p>"}]